messageBody:
Hi. Like most new members, I recently discovered Quikscript and am learning it. I'm
going to be a senior undergrad this fall and intend to use the alphabet to help jot
down how to say all those ridiculously long names I have to learn in Bio class.

But right now I'm frustrated trying to get the fonts I've downloaded to display in Safari
on a Mac. I can type in them on Word and Appleworks but cannot get my browser to
recognize them. With as many people as there are in this forum, can anyone elucidate
the process to me? Thanks a bunch!


~K
